<h2>5 Simple Ways to Connect and Grow</h2><div id="sermon-info" class="sermon"><ul class="sermon-buttons"></ul><!-- .sermon-buttons --><p class="sermon-meta">Posted Aug 7th, 2013 &nbsp;  </p></div><!-- .sermon --><div id="text"><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="social-button-block"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/PortlandChristianCenter" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2270583&amp;fileName=button--facebook-large-0-0-386-63.png" width="386" height="63" alt="GRAPHIC : Button : Facebook Large" title="GRAPHIC : Button : Facebook Large"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://twitter.com/pcctoday" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2270585&amp;fileName=button--twitter-large-0-0-215-63.png" width="215" height="63" alt="GRAPHIC : Button : Twitter Large" title="GRAPHIC : Button : Twitter Large"></a></div><p class="highlight">Feel like you&rsquo;re at the edge of something great,&nbsp;but uncertain what to do next?&nbsp;We want to make your NEXT STEP something easy AND life-changing. Check out an option below and jump into our church family.</p><div id="right_column_ad"><h2>PCCToday is our Monthly Newsletter</h2><br><p><a class="button" href="http://www.pcctoday.com/extras/pcctoday-newsletter/">Sign UP For It Here</a></p><br><h3>First Step Links</h3><ul class="list links"><li><a href="/ministries/adult-education/starting-point/">New? Try Starting Point</a></li><li><a href="/connect-experience/">The CONNECT Experience</a></li><li><a href="/grouplink/">Group Link is Coming!</a></li><li><a href="/baptisms--redirect/">Get Baptized</a></li><li><a href="/adult-ministry-lifelearning--redirect/">Discover Liife Learning: Classes &amp; Groups</a></li><li><a href="/outreach/">Serve in the Community</a></li><li><a href="/giving/">Give Generously</a></li><li><a href="/theprayerwall/">Submit a Prayer Need</a></li></ul></div><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263523&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-1-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 1" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 1" style="margin-right: 25px; margin-bottom: 25px;">Attend a Celebration Service</h4><p>We place a high priority on our two identical <a href="/services/"><strong>Celebration Services</strong></a> each Sunday at 9:00 and 10:45 AM. Worshiping and learning in community with others is one of the best ways to re-align yourself with God.&nbsp;</p><p>Consider this a personal invitation to join us at one of our upcoming&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://pcctalks.wufoo.com/forms/meet-n-greet-rsvp-for-july-21">Meet &lsquo;N Greets</a></strong>&nbsp;after the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/services/" title="Sunday Services 9:00 or 10:45 AM">10:45 AM service</a>. It is here you can spend a few moments with some of our leadership in an "open House" format. Our next Meet 'N Greets are: September 22, November 17.<a href="https://pcctalks.wufoo.com/forms/meet-n-greet-rsvp-for-july-21/" target="_blank"><br></a></p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263527&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-2-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 2" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 2" style="margin-right: 25px; margin-bottom: 25px;">Read the Bible</h4><p>As we read God&rsquo;s Word we begin to see how God responds to life issues and the people around him. Then when we face similar situations as Jesus did, we begin to respond in the same way. This year the entire church is reading through the New Testament using the <a href="/ministries/bible-reading-plan/">5 X 5 X 5 Bible Reading Plan.</a> &nbsp;Check out this excellent plan [<a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/article/2013-bible-reading-plan-its-simplejust-5-x-5-x-5/">here</a>]. You can also read along as&nbsp;<a href="http://www.raynoah.com" target="_blank">Pastor Ray blogs through each passage.</a> You won't want to miss some of his profound insights!</p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263529&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-3-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 3" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 3" style="margin-right: 25px; margin-bottom: 25px;">Pray</h4><p>Prayer is all about two-way communication. Jesus said, &ldquo;Where two or three are gathered in my name, there I am in the midst of them (Matt. 18:20). Practice daily prayer and joining others in one of our many prayer venues. You can also stay informed of the prayer needs of our church or submit your own prayer request at&nbsp;<a href="/theprayerwall/">The Prayer Wall</a>.&nbsp;</p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263543&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-4-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 4" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 4">Join a Class or Small Group</h4><p>Whether it is a&nbsp;<a href="/adult-ministry-lifelearning--redirect/">class</a>&nbsp;or a&nbsp;<a href="/ministries/adult-education/community-life-small-groups/">small group</a>, there are many opportunities to grow and learn together.&nbsp; Be brave&mdash;jump in! &nbsp;Life Learning <a href="/ministries/adult-education/">classes</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="/ministries/adult-education/community-life-small-groups/">groups</a>&nbsp;are offered throughout the week on campus and in host homes. New classes begin every quarter and you are welcome to jump in at any time. &nbsp;See our schedule [<a href="/ministries/adult-education/">here]</a>.</p><p>A simple way to find your way into our church family is to participate in a "come and go" 4-week STARTING POINT from 10:15 to 10:45 AM. This "first experience" opportunity is warmly hosted by Doug and Sherrie MacLardy in the Hospitality Room. Learn more about STARTING POINT.</p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263547&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-5-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 5" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 5">Give Selflessly</h4><p>Giving of your&nbsp;<a href="/outreach/">time, talents,</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="/giving/" target="_blank">treasures</a>&nbsp;pleases the heart of God and fulfills your purpose on this earth. God has a ministry for every one of His children and a mission He has specifically called you to to advance His kingdom. When you selflessly serve with your&nbsp;<a href="/outreach/">time</a>, your&nbsp;<a href="/outreach/">abilities</a>, and your&nbsp;<a href="/giving/">treasure&nbsp;</a>you glorify God.&nbsp;We have many opportunities to <a href="/connect-experience/">discover your gifts</a>, <a href="/giving/">learn about giving generously</a>, and <a href="/outreach/">finding a place to serve</a> in our church, our city, and around the world.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>